{
  "texts": [
    "Hence, we integrate the residual convolutional network with a channel attention strategy.",
    "That focuses on the most representative and discriminative image features, resulting in a computation reduction and performance improvement.",
    "Furthermore, as demonstrated in Fig. 1 (b), the considerable intra-class variability of remote sensing picture scenes makes classification extremely difficult.",
    "Depending on the location, season, or sensor, images in the same category might have a lot of diversity.Generally, deep learning-based strategies can learn sophisticated semantic features and more abstract images and more accurately recognize and describe image scenes, resulting in significant improvements in classification accuracy.",
    "The use of deep learning in image processing has recently experienced considerable growth but still has challenging issues for remote sensing image classification because such methods are mainly concerned with extracting global features while ignoring the crucial objects information in the image.Addressing these challenges requires a shift from traditional mid-level or low-level feature reliance to more sophisticated approaches.In this context, deep learning, particularly convolutional neural networks (CNNs), has emerged as a powerful tool for extracting high-level semantic features from remote sensing images."
  ]
}